Qus1:- Make a Function to add 2 numbers and return the sum.

Code:
import java.util.*;

public class Function {
    public static int calculateSum(int a, int b) {
        int sum = a + b;
        return sum;
    }

    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int sum = calculateSum(a, b);
        System.out.println(sum);
    }
}
//Output a= 3, b = 4 , sum = 7


Qus2:- Make a Function to multiply 2 nummbers and return the product.

Code:-
import java.util.*;

public class Function {
    public static int calculateMultiply(int a, int b) {
        int product = a * b;
        return product;
    }

    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int product = calculateMultiply(a, b);
        System.out.println(product);
    }
}
//Output a= 4, b = 5, product = 20

Qus3: Find the factorial of a Number.

Code:
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {    
    public static int printFactorial(int n) {
        if(n < 0){
        System.out.println("Invalid Number");
        return;
        }
        int factorial = 1;
        for(int i = n; i >= 1; i--){
        factorial = factorial*i;
        System.out.println(factorial);
        return;
        }
        System.out.println(factorial);
        return;
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        printFactorial(n);
    }
}
